ent elementor-element-789e6a8 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-child" data-id="789e6a8" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container"><div class="e-con-inner"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-cdc3403 elementor-toc--content-ellipsis elementor-widget elementor-widget-table-of-contents" data-id="cdc3403" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-settings="{&quot;exclude_headings_by_selector&quot;:[],&quot;marker_view&quot;:&quot;bullets&quot;,&quot;icon&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;library&quot;:&quot;&quot;},&quot;no_headings_message&quot;:&quot;No headings were found on this page.&quot;,&quot;min_height&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:0,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;headings_by_tags&quot;:[&quot;h2&quot;,&quot;h3&quot;,&quot;h4&quot;,&quot;h5&quot;,&quot;h6&quot;],&quot;hierarchical_view&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;,&quot;min_height_laptop&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;min_height_tablet&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;min_height_mobile&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]}}" data-widget_type="table-of-contents.default"><div class="elementor-widget-container"><div id="elementor-toc__cdc3403" class="elementor-toc__body"><div class="elementor-toc__spinner-container"> <svg class="elementor-toc__spinner eicon-animation-spin e-font-icon-svg e-eicon-loading" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 1000 1000" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M500 975V858C696 858 858 696 858 500S696 142 500 142 142 304 142 500H25C25 237 238 25 500 25S975 237 975 500 763 975 500 975Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> </details></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-7d35f86 elementor-widget elementor-widget-theme-post-content" data-id="7d35f86" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="theme-post-content.default"><div class="elementor-widget-container"><p>Many people struggle with earwax buildup and look for simple home remedies to clean their ears. One method that often gets attention is ear candling. Ear candles are hollow cones made of fabric coated in wax, usually beeswax or paraffin. During use, the narrow end of the candle is placed into the ear canal, and the other end is lit on fire.</p><p>The idea is that the flame creates a suction effect, pulling out earwax and other debris. It sounds appealing to people who want an easy, natural fix, but the truth is very different. Research shows that ear candles do not remove earwax and can actually be harmful.</p><p>At America’s Best Hearing, we often see patients who have questions about ear candles or who have even been hurt while using them.&nbsp;</p><p>Our goal is to share what you need to know so you can make safe choices for your hearing health.</p><p>We provide <a href="https://americasbesthearing.com/audiology-services/ear-wax-removal/">professional ear wax removal</a> in Michigan, Minnesota, and Florida.</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Do Ear Candles Really Work?</h2><p>The short answer is no. Studies have shown that ear candling does not produce suction strong enough to pull earwax out of the ear. The residue often found inside the cone after use is not earwax but ash and burned candle material.</p><p>This means that not only does ear candling fail to clean your ears, but it may actually leave behind more debris than you started with.</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Risks of Using Ear Candles</h2><p>While ear candles are marketed as safe and natural, the risks are very real. Some of the most common problems include:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Burns</strong> – Hot wax or flames near the ear and face can cause serious burns.<br></li><li><strong>Blockages</strong> – Melted candle wax can drip into the ear canal, creating a blockage that makes hearing worse.<br></li><li><strong>Ear damage</strong> – Inserting the candle too far can damage the ear canal or eardrum.<br></li><li><strong>Infections</strong> – Blockages and burns can increase the risk of ear infections.<br></li></ul><p>Many people turn to ear candling because they believe it is a safe alternative, but these risks often outweigh any supposed benefit.</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Safer Ways to Manage Earwax</h2><p>Earwax, also called cerumen, is actually good for your ears. It protects the ear canal, traps dirt, and keeps bacteria from causing infections. For most people, earwax naturally works its way out of the ear on its own. But sometimes it builds up and causes problems like muffled hearing, discomfort, or ringing in the ears.</p><p>Instead of using ear candles, here are some safer options:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Professional earwax removal</strong> – Audiologists and hearing instrument specialists use safe tools and methods to remove wax. We provide professional ear wax removal in Michigan, Minnesota, and Florida.<br></li><li><strong>Ear drops</strong> – Over-the-counter drops can soften wax, helping it move out on its own.<br></li><li><strong>Gentle cleaning</strong> – Use a damp cloth to wipe the outer ear only. Never put cotton swabs or other objects inside your ear canal.</li></ul><h2 class="wp-block-heading">When to See a Hearing Professional</h2><p>You should schedule an appointment if you experience:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Sudden or ongoing hearing loss</li><li>Ear pain or pressure</li><li>Persistent ringing in the ears (tinnitus)</li><li>Dizziness or balance problems</li><li>A history of repeated earwax buildup</li></ul><p>At America’s Best Hearing, our audiologists and hearing instrument specialists can safely examine your ears, remove earwax if needed, and check for other conditions that may be causing your symptoms.</p><p>We offer ear wax removal and comprehensive <a href="https://americasbesthearing.com/audiologist-hearing-aids-lansing-mi/">hearing tests in Lansing, MI</a>, New Ulm, MN, Portage, MI, and Sebring, FL.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Why Ear Health Matters</h3><p>Good ear health is about more than just comfort. Blocked ears can interfere with hearing aids, making them less effective. Untreated buildup or damage may also impact your ability to connect with family, friends, and the world around you.</p><p>That is why it is important to seek help from professionals who understand ear health and hearing care. Our team takes the time to listen to your concerns and recommend safe, effective solutions.</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Bottom Line on Ear Candles</h2><p>Ear candles may look like a simple answer, but they do not work and can cause more harm than good. Your ears are delicate, and caring for them requires the right knowledge and tools. If you are worried about earwax buildup or any hearing concerns, the safest choice is to see a hearing professional.</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Professional Ear Wax Removal in Michigan, Minnesota, and Florida</h2><p>If you or someone you love is considering ear candling, we encourage you to think twice. There are safer and more effective options available.</p><p>Schedule an appointment with <a href="https://americasbesthearing.com/">America’s Best Hearing</a>. Let our audiologists and hearing instrument specialists in Michigan, Minnesota, or Florida help you care for your ears the safe way!</p></div></div></div><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-a1c3625 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="a1c3625" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-ea29166 elementor-widget elementor-widget-template" data-id="ea29166" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="template.default"><div class="elementor-widget-container"><div class="elementor-template"><div data-elementor-type="container" data-elementor-id="2